			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Terrorism is like tearing down the Hoover Dam with a pick-axe.  Each individual swing doesn't do much damage but left unchecked that single pickaxe will eventually make a hole and water will come gushing out.
<br />

<br />
If you allow terrorists to blackmail a smaller country, that single incident probably won't effect the U.S. much. However, one small country leads to another and another and another. Eventually, it WILL affect us and everyone else.
<br />

<br />
Target:  Terrorists.  Let's not get cute about definitions and such and how witty you can be on the exactness of who a terrorist is.  We all know it's a gray area and everyone thinks they're so smart for picking apart anyone's attempt at defining who a terrorist is. 
<br />

<br />
Regardless.... the major point I got out of the story was that this country needs to support it's leadership whoever it may be.  When election time comes around, use your vote wisely. But whatever the outcome the American people should support their president. 
<br />

<br />
I prefer a government that is taking action in some way, shape, or form to prevent future attacks rather than one that just responds to attacks after they happen.  Technology and weaponry has forced the world to take a more pre-emptive approach to dealing with terrorism because the results otherwise we have seen can be catastrophic.  Civil liberties are tough to protect when your target doesn't live in any single country and doesn't march in formation or wear a uniform.  It's even tougher when your target looks like every other innocent citizen in the market, hospital, or religious shrine.  Mistakes will be made but I would prefer to see mistakes made rather than just deal with the aftermath.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
