				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Quite simply:  for this article to even be considered any further by me, the author would have to AT LEAST add that they hate us mainly because of our support for Israel.
<br />

<br />
I will expand on this slightly.
<br />

<br />
We feed Israel over $2-billion anually.  This does not even take into consideration the $17-billion in loans that were converted into grants between the 70's and 80's, nor does it take into consideration the $2-billion in private funds that go to Israel as tax writeoffs.
<br />

<br />
Overall I think it totals to $6-billion or more in foreign aid (1/3 of our foreign aid budget).
<br />

<br />
The majority of that money comes right back to the US in return for weapons.
<br />

<br />
We are GIVING them the weapons they use to kill their enemies.  Their enemies have a legitimate beef with us.  There is no doubt about it, there is, and always has been a war going on.  We joined a side of the war, and thus made enemies.  I believe our country did a wise thing to join this side of the war.  I stand firmly by it.  But to say in complete ignorance that the reason we have these enemies is jealousy alone is a BOLD understatement, and it completely destroys the credibility of everything else this man is saying.
<br />

<br />
Jealousy is not the only reason.</span><span class="gensmall"><br /><br />Last edited by Jeal on Thu Jul 29, 2004 8:44 pm; edited 2 times in total</span></td>
